TSHWANE - Public service workers are taking their fight against gender-based violence to the streets of Tshwane. READ: KZN police talk tough on gender-based violence The protest led by the Public Services and Administration department seeks to reinforce President Cyril Ramaphosa's call for all sectors to join the fight. The planned march takes place during Public Service Month, where workers are urged to recommit themselves to the Service Charter. A torch lighting ceremony will be held at the Union Buildings to honour the women killed in the country.